 Communication Strategies for Security Culture
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Apply the Golden Circle model (Why-How-What) to security culture communication
Develop targeted messaging for different organizational stakeholders
Create automated communication workflows using Python
Build a communication plan with scheduling and tracking capabilities
Implement practical tools for ongoing security awareness campaigns
Prerequisites
Basic Python programming knowledge
Understanding of organizational security concepts
Familiarity with Linux command line
Basic knowledge of email protocols and JSON data structures
